    <note>Hu(1) Lian [13135] According to Hu(1) Quan's [10565] funerary inscription for Hu(1) Zi [13142], they shared the same 5th generation ancestor, which would be Hu(2) Shi(2) [13129]. Shi(2), then, was the father of Fu [13131] and Lian and lineal descendant of Hu(1) B [13128] and Hu(1) Yu [13141], Lingyi's [820] father, Bi [18869], was Shi(2)'s lineage kin (tongzu). This would explain why Gongchen was said to have earned the jinshi, but does not appear in the Jian rosters. Gongchen's son, Quan(2) [13138], probably moved to the home of his kinsmen after the fall of Northern Song, and represents jia 'c' of these Hu(1). Hu Quan, WJ, 30.13a.</note>
